62.4	City-state	City-state	A city-state is an independent or autonomous entity whose territory consists of a city which is not administered as a part of another local government. A city-state can also be defined as a central city and its surrounding villages, which together follow the same law, have one form of government, and share languages, religious beliefs, and ways of life.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/View_on_Monacoville.JPG/300px-View_on_Monacoville.JPG
